reviewText:
Since I'm a Sonic fan (PC only at least...) and I saw my friend playing it I thought I could give this game a try and holy cow it was worth it! It's like merge of Sonic and Megaman, but so different, Let me point out few reasons why you should get it:
- Perfect both for casuals and hardcores. Casual and Easy difficulty grat HP regen making the game much easier yet still enjoyable. Normal and Hard are so difficult, that you would be dying A LOT, and especialy near bosses. Thankfuly the game keeps restarting you from the checkpoint so you wouldn't need to do entire stages again;
- It has three completly different playstyles. Words cannot describe it, just watch the trailer;
- Seriously awesome boss fights. Even when I died over 30 times in last boss fights I still had fun... or maybe I'm just weird by having fun being stuck in a boss fights...;
- To me the story is very decent. I usually don't care about it (that's why I don't blame Sonic Team for their... ideas) but here I had a goal to see every damn cutscene;
- Collectibles! Who doesn't like them? And they actualy do something! You will unclock the music (which really stays in your head), voicelines and artwork! That's actualy what I found so far. Who knows what else might be there;
- Don't like the story or just want to play like hardcores in the 90's? Sure thing, get Classic mode and ignore every cutscene or story-related dialogues. (Don't do that please... It is so good);

Now many may wonder: Is this some sort of ripoff? Like some sort of random clone of Sonic or Megaman? NOPE. True, it was heavily inspired on Sonic (that's confirmed, didn't check about Megaman), but gameplay is completly different. How different you may ask? Just look at the trailer! Did you see Sonic driving a motorcycle?! Or maybe Megaman... uhhh... ok you got me there. The only Megaman I played was Megaman Powered Up for PSP but that doesn't change that Freedom Planet is different from it.

So there you have it. Freedom Planet is not a ripoff or clone of any sort, gives amazing experience, is suitable for every fan of platformers and that music! I must get sountrack soon.
Verdict: Buy! NOW! Or wait for sale... your choice but BUY IT!
